It was the day before Thanksgiving when Ronald Livingston looked through the large glass window of the Just a Little Healthier restaurant here and watched an ambulance stop at the white Cape Cod two doors down on West Scott Avenue.
Soon after, a police car came.
And then there was another one.
"Then I saw the medical examiner's boxcar approach", said Livingston, a restaurant supervisor, on Wednesday.
"That's when I knew someone had died".
The hearing learned that the deceased, Olga Arroyo, 41, was an assistant to the director of the Newark Police Department.
Now, investigators are trying to determine if she died from a procedure performed by an unauthorized cosmetic surgeon who was not identified by the police and who worked in the house at 212 West Scott Avenue.
Authorities have not yet determined what caused Ms. Arroyo's death, and they are hopeful that tox screenings, whose results may not be available for weeks, will help unravel a mysterious death that sent a message of mourning to the Newark Police Department.
