"She was my pit bull.
She protected me".
McCarthy said that Mrs. Arroyo was the wife of Jimmy Arroyo, a former New York City police officer who works for the Alcohol Control Commission, and that she leaves behind two sons, 14 and 11, and a stepdaughter.
Eileen Walsh, a spokeswoman for Union County District Attorney Theodore J. Romankow, said investigators would be trying to determine if Arroyo died as a result of an unauthorized surgical procedure.
"That's one of the possibilities", said Mrs. Walsh.
"It's an ongoing investigation".
Authorities said they arrived at the house around 3 p.m. in November.
And they found Mrs. Arroyo on a couch.
She was pronounced dead on the scene.
More than a week has passed and the authorities have given little information about their investigation or the owner of the house, listed as Flor Margarita Castro.
Walsh wouldn't say if Mrs. Castro was being questioned by the authorities.
Investigators are trying to determine if a part of the house was used as a medical practice.
On Wednesday, no one opened the door to Mrs. Castro's house, where a weakened rose bush stands in the narrow front yard and a Dalmatian barks behind the house.
